LAST-MODIFIED:20260310T121818Z
UID:10007424-1774119600-1774126800@unitedarts.org
SUMMARY:Symphonic Favorites - Triangle Pride Symphonic Band Spring 2026 Concert
DESCRIPTION:Join the Triangle Pride Band in celebrating the art of symphonic band music that has helped define the genre. From classrooms to rehearsal halls\, these influential composers and works have shaped the concert band tradition over the last century. This program features music by acclaimed composers such as Eric Whitacre and Leonard Bernstein\, alongside enduring wind ensemble staples like Arabesque. \nFree admission for children four and under.
URL:https://unitedarts.org/calendar/symphonic-favorites-triangle-pride-symphonic-band-spring-2026-concert/
LOCATION:Garner Magnet High School\, 2101 Spring Dr\, Garner\, 27529
CATEGORIES:Concert
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://unitedarts.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/unnamed.png
ORGANIZER;CN="triangle pride band":MAILTO:info@triangleprideband.com
END:VEVENT
