UID:10007033-1774173600-1774195200@unitedarts.org
SUMMARY:Women Only - One Day Workshop: Sewing 101
DESCRIPTION:When: Sunday\, March 22\, 10 am – 4 pm \nWhere: The Joel Fund \nIf you have ever been intimidated to learn to sew on a sewing machine\, now is your chance to learn with The Joel Fund! In the no-nonsense class\, instructor Grace McFetters Caldwell will take you through the basic mechanics of your sewing machine\, then teach you how to use it step-by-step. Students will learn the fundamentals of sewing in easy to digest project that will have their confidence up so they are ready to head home and conquer their own sewing projects! \nPlease Note: All classes and workshops are for Military Connected women who are 18 years or older. \nPLEASE NOTE: Typically\, TJF fiber arts classes and workshops are for women only\, but this workshop is open to any military-connected individual.
URL:https://unitedarts.org/calendar/women-only-one-day-workshop-sewing-101/
LOCATION:The Joel Fund\, 822 S White Street\, Wake Forest\, 27587
ORGANIZER;CN="The Joel Fund":MAILTO:isabella@thejoelfund.org
END:VEVENT
